  "text": "see e.g. [CITATION_1] . Our next task is to prove this expansion indeed holds true and to derive an expression for the offset \u03ba \u221e when the process (F n , G n ) n\u2208Z is further assumed to be a Markov process satisfying some regularity and moment assumptions. Namely, consider for any n \u2208 Z the \u03c3 -field F n := \u03c3 ((F k , G k ) : k \u2264 n) and assume there exists a transition kernel P :",
